	"nodes":[
		{"id":"a6d81e3ad98ff343","type":"text","text":"## Project Status: VNME (Vietnamese Learning App)\n\n### What You Have (A Lot)\n\n**Frontend (vnme-app):** React 19 + Vite, mobile-optimized (480px), 5-tab bottom nav\n\n**8 Practice Modules built:**\n\n- Tone Practice, Vowels, Numbers, Tone Marks, TELEX Typing, Pronouns/Kinship, Vocabulary (SRS), Pitch Training\n\n**Tabs built:**\n\n- Roadmap (4 units), Practice selector, Dictionary (with TTS), Grammar reference, Leaderboard (placeholder)\n\n**Gamification:** Dong currency system, daily streaks, module unlocking, XP rewards\n\n**Backend:** Express + SQLite with dictionary search (758K EN-VN words, 91K ZH-VN words)\n\n**Data (vnme-data):** 1.4GB EN dictionary DB, 150MB ZH dictionary DB, 13K+ grammar entries, 100+ curated vocab words\n\n**Admin CMS:** Roadmap Mapper, Lesson Builder, Grammar Editor\n\n---\n\n### What's Missing for MVP\n\nThe app has many features started but few are **complete end-to-end**. Here's what I'd prioritize for a shippable MVP:\n\n|Priority|Gap|Why Critical|\n|---|---|---|\n|1|**Lesson flow doesn't work** - `LessonGame.jsx` is minimal, roadmap nodes don't lead to real lessons|Core loop is broken - users can't actually learn|\n|2|**No SRS/review system** - vocab practice exists but no spaced repetition scheduling|Users forget everything without review|\n|3|**No progress persistence** - everything in localStorage, schema.sql exists but isn't wired up|Progress lost on device change/clear|\n|4|**Practice modules lack completion → reward flow** - some modules don't properly award dong/XP|Gamification loop is broken|\n|5|**No onboarding → first lesson funnel** - onboarding collects data but doesn't guide to content|Users don't know what to do first|\n|6|**Leaderboard is empty**|Tab exists but does nothing|\n\n---\n\n### Recommended MVP Scope (Critical Path)\n\nWant me to build a plan focusing on these **3 pillars** for a working MVP?\n\n1. **Core Learning Loop** - Roadmap node → Lesson → Exercises → Score → Reward → Next node\n2. **Review System** - Simple SRS for vocabulary learned in lessons\n3. **Polish & Connect** - Wire up onboarding → first lesson, fix gamification rewards, remove/hide unfinished features\n\nThis would give you a **usable app** where someone can: open it → onboard → start learning Vietnamese through structured lessons → review vocabulary → see progress → come back daily.\n\nShould I create a detailed implementation plan for this MVP, or do you want to adjust the scope first?\n\n--------------\n## MVP Implementation Complete\n\n### Phase 1: Core Learning Loop (wired end-to-end)\n\n- **LessonGame** now tracks score, streak, best streak during exercises\n- On lesson completion: awards dong via `DongContext.addDong()`, marks the roadmap node as completed via `completeNode()`, and adds learned words to SRS\n- Shows actual reward breakdown (base + accuracy + perfect + streak bonuses) and learned words on the completion screen\n- **TTS** wired to all audio buttons — listen_choose, dictation, speaking_repeat exercises now play Vietnamese pronunciation\n- **Dynamic node status** — nodes are computed from `completedNodes` in DongContext instead of static INIT_DATA, so completing a lesson immediately unlocks the next node\n\n### Phase 2: Content (2 full units)\n\n- **Unit 2: Coffee Culture** added with 3 lessons (Cafe Ordering, Vietnamese Food, How Much?)\n- 18 new exercises across 6 types (MCQ, listen_choose, reorder, diacritics, dictation, match_pairs)\n- 18 new vocabulary items with translations (ca phe sua da, pho, banh mi, bao nhieu tien, etc.)\n- DB key bumped to `vnme_mock_db_v3` to force re-init\n\n### Phase 3: SRS Review System\n\n- New [srs.js](vscode-webview://02eig00g4vti4dogn6p888f80s69hlbl5uookipev6p21stg2eqq/src/lib/srs.js) — spaced repetition with intervals: 1→3→7→14→30 days\n- Words automatically added to SRS when lessons are completed\n- New **Review tab** in VocabPractice (now the first tab) with due count badge\n- Review banner on RoadmapTab: \"X words to review\" when items are due\n- Review quiz awards dong on completion\n\n### Phase 4: Polish\n\n- **Onboarding data saved** — goal, dialect, level, dailyMins now persist to UserContext\n- **TopBar** shows real streak and dong balance from DongContext (no more hardcoded values)\n- **Profile** in settings shows actual user data from UserContext\n- **RewardToast** — slide-up notification for dong earned and daily streak bonuses\n- **LeaderboardTab** replaced with clean \"Coming Soon\" placeholder\n- **Pronouns** module un-commented in PracticeTab\n\n### Files Modified/Created\n\n|File|Status|\n|---|---|\n|[LessonGame.jsx](vscode-webview://02eig00g4vti4dogn6p888f80s69hlbl5uookipev6p21stg2eqq/src/components/LessonGame.jsx)|Rewritten — score, rewards, TTS, word summary|\n|[db.js](vscode-webview://02eig00g4vti4dogn6p888f80s69hlbl5uookipev6p21stg2eqq/src/lib/db.js)|Unit 2 content, dynamic nodes, helper functions|\n|[RoadmapTab.jsx](vscode-webview://02eig00g4vti4dogn6p888f80s69hlbl5uookipev6p21stg2eqq/src/components/Tabs/RoadmapTab.jsx)|Dynamic progress, review banner|\n|[VocabPractice.jsx](vscode-webview://02eig00g4vti4dogn6p888f80s69hlbl5uookipev6p21stg2eqq/src/pages/Practice/VocabPractice.jsx)|SRS Review tab|\n|[srs.js](vscode-webview://02eig00g4vti4dogn6p888f80s69hlbl5uookipev6p21stg2eqq/src/lib/srs.js)|**New** — spaced repetition engine|\n|[RewardToast.jsx](vscode-webview://02eig00g4vti4dogn6p888f80s69hlbl5uookipev6p21stg2eqq/src/components/RewardToast.jsx)|**New** — toast notifications|\n|[TopBar.jsx](vscode-webview://02eig00g4vti4dogn6p888f80s69hlbl5uookipev6p21stg2eqq/src/components/TopBar.jsx)|Real stats from context|\n|[OnboardingFlow.jsx](vscode-webview://02eig00g4vti4dogn6p888f80s69hlbl5uookipev6p21stg2eqq/src/components/Onboarding/OnboardingFlow.jsx)|Saves preferences|\n|[UserContext.jsx](vscode-webview://02eig00g4vti4dogn6p888f80s69hlbl5uookipev6p21stg2eqq/src/context/UserContext.jsx)|Added onboarding fields|\n|[LeaderboardTab.jsx](vscode-webview://02eig00g4vti4dogn6p888f80s69hlbl5uookipev6p21stg2eqq/src/components/Tabs/LeaderboardTab.jsx)|Coming Soon placeholder|\n|[PracticeTab.jsx](vscode-webview://02eig00g4vti4dogn6p888f80s69hlbl5uookipev6p21stg2eqq/src/components/Tabs/PracticeTab.jsx)|Pronouns enabled|\n|[App.jsx](vscode-webview://02eig00g4vti4dogn6p888f80s69hlbl5uookipev6p21stg2eqq/src/App.jsx)|RewardToast, removed hardcoded stats|\n\n**Note:** Since the DB key was bumped to v3, you'll need to clear localStorage (or use a fresh browser) to see the new Unit 2 content. The old v2 data will be ignored and fresh data will initialize.","x":-1487,"y":-690,"width":907,"height":688},
		{"id":"977c4f432ce4e0a3","type":"text","text":"Here's the licensing breakdown:\n\n|Dictionary|License|Commercial Use?|Risk|\n|---|---|---|---|\n|**VE** (FVDP - Ho Ngoc Duc)|**GPL**|Yes, with copyleft|LOW|\n|**3-dict-combination** (VI-VI)|**GPL + CC BY-SA**|Yes, with share-alike|LOW-MEDIUM|\n|mtBab-VE|Proprietary (scraped bab.la)|No|HIGH|\n|Prodic_Business|Proprietary (EConTech)|No|HIGH|\n|Prodic_Technical|Proprietary (EConTech)|No|HIGH|\n|Prodict_4in1_all|Proprietary (EConTech)|No|HIGH|\n|Hán Việt (hanviet.csv)|Unknown|Unclear|MEDIUM-HIGH|\n|JaViDic_VJ|Proprietary (EConTech)|No|HIGH|\n|mtBab_VF|Proprietary (Lac Viet MTD)|No|HIGH|\nThe Vietnamese-Chinese dictionary (`mtBabVC`) is also **not safe for commercial use**.\n\n|Dictionary|Source|License|Commercial?|\n|---|---|---|---|\n|mtBabVC (Simplified)|Converted by dangquybk from **Lac Viet** commercial data|**Proprietary**|No|\n|mtBabVC (Traditional)|Same source|**Proprietary**|No|\n\nThe converter (dangquybk) explicitly described his work as \"converting\" existing dictionaries — the underlying data comes from Lac Viet's commercial dictionary. The OVDP SourceForge project claims GPLv2, but that doesn't override the original copyright.\n\n**Updated full picture — only these are commercially usable:**\n\n|#|Dictionary|License|OK?|\n|---|---|---|---|\n|1|VE (FVDP)|GPL|Yes (copyleft)|\n|6|3-dict-combination (VI-VI)|GPL + CC BY-SA|Yes (copyleft)|\n|—|_Everything else_|Proprietary/Unknown|No|\n\nIf you want a commercially clean alternative for Chinese-Vietnamese, the research found **[CVDICT](https://github.com/ph0ngp/CVDICT)** which is explicitly **CC BY-SA 4.0** licensed. That could replace the current mtBab ZH data.\n\n**Only 2 are clearly safe for commercial use:**\n\n1. **VE** (Free Vietnamese Dictionary Project by Ho Ngoc Duc) — GPL licensed. You can use it commercially but must share your modifications under GPL.\n2. **3-dict-combination** (Vietnamese-Vietnamese) — GPL + CC BY-SA mix. Same copyleft requirement.\n\nThe rest are proprietary data from EConTech (Prodic, JaViDic), Lac Viet (mtBab_VF), or bab.la (mtBab-VE) — all scraped/repackaged commercial dictionaries without redistribution rights. The Hán Việt CSV has no identifiable license.\n\nIf you want a commercially clean deployment, you'd need to strip out sources 2-5, 7, 8, and 9, keeping only VE and the 3-dict-combination. Want me to do that?\n\nBased on the data in your `raw` folder, there are a few open-source dictionaries, but **none of them have a permissive license that allows for easy use in a closed-source commercial product.**\n\nHere is the breakdown of the ones that are open-source or freely available:\n\n### 1. Open Source (GPL License)\n\nThese dictionaries are from the **Open Vietnamese Dictionaries Project** (Từ điển Tiếng Việt miễn phí của Hồ Ngọc Đức):\n\n- `Từ điển Tiếng Việt` (Viet-Viet)\n- `Free Korean-Vietnamese Dictionary`\n- `Free German-Vietnamese Dictionary`\n\n**Can you use them commercially?** **Yes, BUT with a major condition.** They are licensed under the **GPL (GNU General Public License)**. This is a \"copyleft\" license, meaning if you use this data in your application, **your entire application must also be open-sourced under the GPL license**. If your goal is to build a proprietary, closed-source commercial app, you cannot use these databases.\n\n### 2. Academic / Non-Commercial\n\n- `Lexical Database of Vietnamese`: This dataset is strictly licensed under **CC BY-NC 4.0** (Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial). It is explicitly **not for commercial use** and is meant purely for academic research.\n\n### 3. Unknown License (High Legal Risk)\n\n- `en_vi` and `star_vietanh`: These files do not have explicit authors or licenses attached to them. Because their origin and copyright status are unverified, using them in a commercial product is highly legally risky.\n\n### **Conclusion**\n\nIf you are planning to build a closed-source, proprietary commercial app, **there is currently no database in this folder that you can safely and legally use.**\n\nTo build a commercial dictionary without open-sourcing your code, you will need to find a database with a permissive license (like **MIT, Apache 2.0,** or **CC-BY**) or license one directly from a commercial provider (like EConTech or Lạc Việt).","x":233,"y":-638,"width":895,"height":578},
		{"id":"6acc915958cbe8df","type":"text","text":"Here are the best options given what's already in your codebase:                                                                                       \n                                                                                                                                                         \n  1. Grammar Explorer (highest impact, zero new content needed)                                                                                          \n  - vn_grammar_bank.json already has A1+ grammar patterns with explanations, examples, and FAQs                                                          \n  - Browsable list → tap a pattern → see structure, examples with TTS, usage notes                                                                       \n  - Could replace the Watch tab or live under Practice                                                                                                   \n  - Unique differentiator — most Vietnamese apps skip grammar entirely                                                                                   \n\n  2. Sentence Builder drill (gamified, uses existing data)                                                                                               \n  - Pull sentences from lessons.json dialogues and vn_grammar_bank.json examples                                                                         \n  - Scramble word order → user drags/taps words into correct Vietnamese sentence order\n  - Teaches grammar intuitively through word-ordering (like Duolingo's signature exercise)\n  - Works entirely from data already on disk\n\n  3. Real SRS for Vocabulary (sticky retention feature)\n  - VocabPractice already claims \"Dynamic SRS\" in the UI but doesn't implement it\n  - Add localStorage-based spaced repetition: track correct/incorrect, resurface weak words\n  - Turns a one-time browse into a daily habit loop — critical for MVP retention\n\n  4. Listening Comprehension quiz (leverages TTS you already have)\n  - Play a Vietnamese sentence via TTS → user picks the correct English/Chinese translation from 4 choices\n  - Can generate questions from dictionary examples and lesson dialogues automatically\n  - No audio files needed, no external APIs\n\n  My recommendation for the Watch tab slot: Grammar Explorer. It fills the biggest content gap, needs no new data, and is the kind of feature users\n  search for (\"Vietnamese grammar\") that competitors handle poorly. The Sentence Builder could then be a new Practice module.","x":-40,"y":-40,"width":876,"height":751},
